re several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margrethe de Podebuz was born about 1225, in Putbus, Rügen, Pomerania, Prussia, Germany, her father, Nicolaus de Podebusk, was 8 and her mother, Mrs. Nicolau von Podebusk, was 37. She had at least 4 sons and 6 daughters with Stoislaw von Vilmnitz Putbus II."},"et":{"ABT. 1225–UNKNOWN":"umbes 1225–Surnud","1221–1253":"1221–1253","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1217–1278":"1217–1278","1245–Female":"1245–Surnud","1247–1295":"1247–1295","1249–Female":"1249–Surnud","1252–1311":"1252–1311","1252–1314":"1252–1314","1253–1315":"1253–1315","1253–1296":"1253–1296","1254–Female":"1254–Surnud","1255–Female":"1255–Surnud","1256–Male":"1256–Surnud","1218–1315":"1218–1315","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1190":"1190","1253":"1253","1296":"1296","1252":"1252","1295":"1295","ABT 1219":"umbes 1219","1217":"1217","1315":"1315","1249":"1249","1314":"1314","1247":"1247","1225":"1225","1256":"1256","1311":"1311","1245":"1245","1278":"1278","1255":"1255","1254":"1254","1221":"1221","ABT. 1225":"umbes 1225","1218":"1218","of Borantehangen and Putbus, Rugen, Pomerania":"Putbus, Rügen, Pommern, Freistaat Preußen, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"ABT. 1225–UNKNOWN":"noin 1225–Kuollut","1221–1253":"1221–1253","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1217–1278":"1217–1278","1245–Female":"1245–Kuollut","1247–1295":"1247–1295","1249–Female":"1249–Kuollut","1252–1311":"1252–1311","1252–1314":"1252–